<title type="html"><![CDATA[Royal台北星期四文章 • 5/4(Thu)Religious Cult: The Story of FLDS and its Leader: Warren Jeffs／How do you feel in crowds? (Host: Louie)]]></title>

<category term="Royal台北星期四文章" scheme="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewforum.php?f=3" label="Royal台北星期四文章"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=725&amp;p=753#p753"><![CDATA[
5/4(Thu)Religious Cult: The Story of FLDS and its Leader: Warren Jeffs／How do you feel in crowds? (Host: Louie)<br /><br />We will hold an on-site meeting only.<br /><br />摩斯漢堡明曜店(每人低消 :60元)<br />台北市仁愛路4段151巷37號地下室.<br />MRT忠孝敦化站3號出口 , 明曜百貨後方第二個巷子口<br /><br />Royal 台北 ( Thursday )<br />**** NEW*** Meeting time agenda:7:00-9:00 PM<br />7:00-7:30 Chatting time with your favorite drink, and introduction of the meeting by the host<br />7:30-8:00 discussion of the first topic<br />8:00-8:05 Take a group photo<br />8:05-8:30 discussion of the second topic<br />8:30-9:00 Individual Presentation (each person will have two minutes to give a presentation on any topic of that day. <br />)<br /><br />--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session 1: Religious Cult: The Story of FLDS and its Leader: Warren Jeffs<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.esquire.com/uk/culture/a40151990/the-true-story-of-keep-sweet-pray/">https://www.esquire.com/uk/culture/a401 ... weet-pray/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br /><br />1.Have you ever heard about any mysterious religious cult (local or abroad), what do you think about them?<br />2.How come are these believers so gullible? In your point of view.<br />3.Fragile minds are vulnerable to injuries and that’s when the evil takes advantage on. What should we do to prevent people from falling into pitfalls of devils?<br />4.What is the similarity between a religious cult and autocracy in ruling the public?<br /><br /><br />Session 2: Are you lonely in a crowd?<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/learningenglish/english/features/6-minute-english_2023/ep-230323">https://www.bbc.co.uk/learningenglish/e ... /ep-230323</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br /><br />1.Do you find correlation between this article and the one in session 1?<br />2.When people get together in a crowd, they become irrational, why?<br />3.You must have participated in any kinds of group activities before. What kind of activity gives you the feeling that you are part of them and share the same value? What made you feel lonely?<br />4.Do you feel alone, awkward and alienated in a big crowd? What would you do to improve it (if you need to stay for some reason)?<br /><br /><br /><br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次(含實體及線上會議)後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放的心與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38674">Louie Wang</a> — Sat Apr 29, 2023 11:24 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
