03/30 (Thu) 10 Dangerous Food Safety Mistakes  / Safety Tips to Memorize Before Your Next Flight (Host: Joyce)<br />We will hold an on-site meeting only.<br /><br />摩斯漢堡明曜店(每人低消 :60元)<br />台北市仁愛路4段151巷37號地下室.<br />MRT忠孝敦化站3號出口 , 明曜百貨後方第二個巷子口<br /><br />Royal 台北 ( Thursday )<br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:30 pm ：opening ＆free talk<br />7:30-8:00 pm: session I, the first topic, subgroup discussion<br />8:00-8:30 pm: session 2, the second topic ,subgroup discussion.<br />8:30-9:00 table topic<br /><br />--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Article 1:</span> 10 Dangerous Food Safety Mistakes <br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.cdc.gov/foodsafety/ten-dangerous-mistakes.html">https://www.cdc.gov/foodsafety/ten-dang ... takes.html</a><!-- m --><br />Question:<br />1.What kind of mistake can lead to serious foodborne illness?<br />2.What things you should never make in your Instant Pot to avoid serious illness, and how to keep yourself safe when preparing this type of food?<br />3.How long is it safe to eat leftovers? How to tell whether food has gone bad?<br />4.Is microwaving food safe? Does using a microwave to cook ruin the nutrients in food?<br />5.Does food cooked in a microwave taste any different from the same food cooked in an oven?<br /><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Article 2: </span>11 Safety Tips to Memorize Before Your Next Flight<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.travelandleisure.com/travel-tips/travel-warnings/airplane-emergency-tips">https://www.travelandleisure.com/travel ... gency-tips</a><!-- m --><br />Question:<br />1. Do you dare to drink hot water, coffee or tea on a plane? Or do you only drink liquids that come in a can or bottle?<br />2. What things should we do to be better prepared which will make every flight more pleasant, while improving our odds in the highly unlikely event of an emergency?<br />3. What to do if an airline damages or loses your luggage?<br />4.How true is the &quot;last in first out&quot; concept for checked in luggage?<br />5.Does the priority tag on checked suitcase make a difference? Is it true that the handlers deliberately ignore priority baggage tags?<br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次(含實體及線上會議)後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放的心與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=55735">zoe</a> — Fri Mar 24, 2023 7:12 pm</p><hr />
